name: Kentucky Coffeetree Cafe
directions: Very back of reataurant, on the left.
comment: For paying customers; buy a cheap coffee or pastry and you can stay there as long as you need.

name: Square Books
directions: Upstairs, take a right. By the history books
comment: A pretty inclusive place over all, spend some time here if you can

name: Booze Dining Hall at Slippery Rock University
directions: In the from lobby area, on the left

name: Baily Library at Slippery Rock University
directions: Several places, but easiest is on the first floor, around the corner from the women's restroom (it will be in kind of a small hallway that has display cases of books and leads into the first floor Library area and the vending and snack area).

name: Morrow Field House at Slippery Rock University
directions: Two side-by-side on the top floor, near a few classrooms

name: Next Generation Connecticut Hall
directions: Several all gender single stalls on first floor (by game room, down the hall toward classrooms next to offices). Also two downstairs by classrooms.

name: Slippery Rock Univerity Smith Student Center
directions: On both the second and third floors, next to the gendered bathrooms and water fountain, beside the elevators and behind the stairs. There are signs pointing where the restrooms are.
comment: SRU has a number of other gender-neutral restrooms, including in Boozel Dining Hall, the library, and the Field House.

name: Aquarium world
comment: They don't seem to care too much. It's behind all of the fish tank accessories

name: Nervous Dog Coffee Bar
directions: There are two, both right by the counter.
comment: You don't have to be a customer, but their coffee is good and the baristas are really nice.

name: Perpich Center for Arts Education
directions: There are 3- one directly in the first building, up the stairs and to the right. The other two are in a separate building behind the other and to the left, the Gaia building, directly inside.
comment: In the school, you must sign in as a visitor. In the Gaia building, you do not.

name: Slippery Rock University Student Center
directions: In the Smith Student Center, by the water fountain and gendered restrooms on the second and third floors.
comment: SRU also has a number of gender-neutral restrooms in various buildings across campus, in including in the library, boozel dining hall, and the field house.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store
comment: No one has ever asked me to be a paying customer

name: HERBARIUM
directions: Door in building lobby marked "Private". Go down stairs and follow hallway. Gendered signs on bathrooms but no one actually cares who uses which. Women's room has 2 private stalls, Mens has stall & urinal.
comment: Bathroom is not in store, but part of the building itself.

name: NCAD Gallary
directions: Enter via Thomas street through the rounded arch, turn left and enter the first glass doors to your left. Keep straight past the stairs and turn left into an open space with a reception desk along the left. The gender neutral toilet stall is also on the left between the reception desk and the elevator. Ahead is a open doorway to the NCAD Gallery space which has a glass wall facing Thomas Street traffic.
comment:
NCAD is open:
8am-9pm term time.
9am-5pm holiday/summer time.
Closed at weekends.
(If blue doors are completely shut at archway, it's closed).

It is inside the college grounds, but by the public gallery space. I went to college there for 4 years and was never once asked for my student card, still frequent there and they have a public cafe, etc. The age range of the college is vast, with tonnes of mature students up to and exceeding 60 yrs old. Do not be afraid, just act like you are supposed to be there or visiting a friend.

It is a single non gendered stall, fitted out for disabled access but not specifically for disabled only.

name: MTSU Student Union Building
directions: On the first floor down the hallway past the elevators, with the other restrooms

name: Old Navy
comment: The doors are gendered, but no one cares. The employees regularly use both bathrooms. Also it's back by the employees only room, so the only people back there are people who really have to pee and employees who won't judge or harass.

name: Grow the Produce shop
directions: There are 2 single stall unisex restrooms in the back of the shop. Both are ADA compliant except not really because one of the two restrooms has a narrow hallway leading to it.
comment: Just ask an employee for directions to the restroom, you don't have to buy anything but it would be nice if you did.

name: Dalhousie Forrest Building
directions: Floor G beside elevator and the female washroom

name: Harvard Law school - pound hall
directions: In the basement, take the elevator down and turn right
comment: Open to public from about 7.30am to 6pm, after that you need a Harvard ID card for the elevator o work.

name: Dalhousie Dentistry Building
directions: Many of the eight washrooms unmarked. First floor washroom is beside the J. D. McLean Centre sign. Second floor is beside the Carleton Computer Lab sign.
comment: Open to the Dalhousie community.

name: Dalhousie University, Clinical Research Centre
directions: First two floors. Follow signs to washrooms.

name: Milwaukee Institute of Art & Design
directions: Each floor has a gender neutral bathroom, closest one upon entering the building is to the left.
comment: You'll need a school ID to enter past 6PM, otherwise everyone there is very considerate of trans and gender non conforming individuals!

name: Dalhousie University, Marion McCain Arts and Social Sciences Building
directions: Up the half-flight of stairs (or elevator) from the front lobby to the mezzanine - there is one single-room officially gender-neutral bathroom on either side of the open space.
comment: Students everywhere, no-one looks or cares. One of the two is often closed for repairs (it varies which one), but not both at the same time. May be very busy on weekday afternoons around the half-hour (class change times).

name: Starbucks
directions: In the door by the parking lot, into the little hallway.

name: Biggby Coffee
directions: Through the back door are two gendered restrooms. Both single room bathrooms.
comment: They don't care which bathroom you use. I've been able to use the mens bathroom every time I go there.

name: Schmizza Pub and Grub in Cedar Hills
directions: To the left of the front counter, other wall is a bank of windows. Next to self-serve soda fountain. Area might be crowded if patrons are selecting pizza toppings or filling sodas.
comment: The single stalls are marked as men's  and women's but the doors are painted in chalkboard paint with designs indicating that they are gender neutral and safe. Bathroom doors require a key, available near the front counter. Might be a bit high-traffic for some, but could be a good option.

name: Arsaga's at the Depot
directions: inside at the opposite end of the coffee counter
comment: i don't know if you have to be a paying customer, the staff tends to be pretty chill so you could probably just go in and out without trouble

name: Esquire Theatre
directions: Down the hallway in the back, directly across from the small bar.
comment: If you're a "paying customer" you'll be totally fine. It might be more difficult if you aren't simply because the bathroom is past concessions and they might suspect you're trying to sneak into a movie. But if if you're comfortable enough to ask to use the gender neutral restroom in the back most of the employees probably wouldn't care at all.

name: Oregon Public House
directions: Straight back past the bar and to the right.
comment: Friendly community space. Paying customers preferred but not required or enforced.

name: Quince
directions: Back of the dining room
comment: For diners and bar guests

name: The East Bay Depot for Creative Reuse
directions: The bathroom key is at the register, the bathroom is all the way in the back of the store

name: Lone Star Saloon
directions: All the way in the back of the bar
comment: 21 and over only. This is a trans friendly, gay bear bar.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Back right of the store
comment: 2 bathrooms, both gender-neutral.

name: The Fresh Market
directions: As soon as you walk into the building, make a left. Both restrooms are at the end of the hallway.
comment: They're technically gendered, but there are no stalls. They're both single bathrooms, the men's does not have a urinal. Employees will alternate between bathrooms, I've seen customers do this too!

name: Five Below
directions: Back of the store, behind the Employees Only door(need to ask employee permission).
comment: You have to ask an employee for permission to use the restroom, since they're technically employee-only, but 95% of the time customers are permitted to use them as well. (They're often closed to customers during the Christmas season due to stock room overflow into the bathroom area that leads to safety issues for customers, though, be aware.) Toilets are single-person and gender-neutral; there are residual gendered signs but all customers are directed to use the same bathroom regardless of gender. (The other one is either for employees only or for storage.)

name: Dave's Sushi
directions: Immediately to the right when you walk in

name: North Carolina Hillel
directions: Take the elevator or stairs (both are to your left as you enter, elevator a little farther in), and then  the bathrooms are to the left of the balcony.
comment: You'll need to ring the doorbell to get in, because of precautions against antisemitic violence, but you're more than welcome to come and have a safe space to use the bathroom.

name: North Carolina Hillel
directions: Second floor (accessible elevator), to the left of the balcony
comment: You'll need to ring the doorbell to get inside because of precautions about antisemitic violence, but you're totally welcome to come in and use the bathroom.

name: Parker
directions: I know there's at least one on the middle floor.

name: University Center UNCO
directions: Second floor, next to the ballrooms

name: Argo Tea
directions: Two single stall gender neutral bathrooms, both accessible
comment: Code on receipt, ask for it at register

name: Square One Food Court
directions: Signs above food court point to gender-neutral bathrooms.

name: Iba Hall
directions: First floor by the elevators

name: Argo Tea
directions: Need key
comment: Ask for the key at the register

name: University Of Lincoln, Tower Bar
directions: Straight line from the door.
comment: Not open all the time but it's a student bar so they're used to people popping in and out.

name: Gnomon School of Visual Effects
directions:
-Bathroom by Lab 6/Sculpture is single stall
-Bathroom by drawing room is single stall

name: Quality Food Center
directions: In the dairy section at the very right back of the store, you go through black double doors and go right through another door and down a short hallway. The single restroom is on the left.
comment:
It's not likely that anyone will object if you're not a paying customer and use the restroom. The staff are generally nice/quiet. If you just walk in, even without buying anything, and ask someone who works there for directions to the bathroom, they will probably give it to you.

The bathroom is in a "behind-the-scenes" sort of area within the store. It is quiet and feels separated from the rest of the store.

name: Half Price Books
directions: Far back right corner, through the clearance section.

name: Harvard Westlake School
directions: First floor of Munger library.
comment: Only accessible when the school is open.

name: Goodwill
directions: To the left as soon as you come in the front door and you'll see it between the other 2 bathrooms.

name: Lincoln High School
directions: Both sides of the first floor of the main building

name: Lincoln High School
directions: Both sides of the first floor of the main building

name: Biblioteca Tecla Sala
directions: Hay que subir una rampa muy larga para entrar a la recepción de la biblioteca, y una vez dentro hacia la derecha están los baños. Hay más arriba dentro de la biblioteca, accesible por unas escaleras que se ven enseguida o un ascensor que hay al fondo mirando desde donde entras a la biblo.
comment: Todo el mundo puede acceder gratis.

name: Camera 7 Cinema
directions: Theres a unisex handicap bathroom on the first floor
comment: You have to be a customer but I think theres also one at PMH next door

name: Victor's 1959 Cafe
directions: In the front entryway, red door

name: Totto Ramen
directions: Straight back once you enter.
comment: There are two bathrooms (no stalls, just a single-person bathroom) with no gendered signs out front. In a fairly liberal area. No signs say so, but you most likely need to be a paying customer.

name: Lollicup
directions: Straight in the back

name: @nerdvana coffee shop
directions: Green doors

name: Mochi on Archer
comment: Use the bathroom and then sample some yogurt to act interested before leaving.

name: Bangor Mall
comment: Family Restroom (parents with young children but anyone can use it)

name: Starbucks
comment: Paying customers only

name: Starbucks
comment: Paying customers only

name: Dutchess Community College
directions: To the right if you're exiting the cooking area itself.  It should be across the benches and labeled. c:

name: FAU All-Night Study Area
directions: On the second floor, which can be accessed by either the elevator or the staircase. There are two gender neutral/family stalls. Each is its own room and they are placed next to each other.
comment: I think this study area is located in the Hillel building, just on the 2nd floor. (Not 100% sure)

name: Trent University
directions: Located in Gzowski College in the cafeteria

name: Trent University
directions: It's in Otonabee College, just past Wenjack theatre. It is located next to the women's washroom.

name: Pier 1 Imports
directions: To your right once you enter, between bays of pillows.

name: Bodegoes
directions: Main floor, around corner from mirror
comment: I work here and am transgender, we're currently working on getting unisex bathroom signs for the door

name: Kindness & Mischief Coffee
directions: At the back of the coffee shop.

name: Cornell College
directions: One is on the middle floor (2 button in elevator) and there are two on the bottom floor (1 button in elevator).

name: Batten Arts & Letters Building
directions: Second floor, down the hall to the left are three gender inclusive single stalls. Also accessible by elevator.

name: Lil Pantry White City
directions: In same building as carwash

name: Dragas Hall
directions: Second floor, the closest hall next to the stairs, take a left until you see it on the right. Also accessible by elevator.

name: Springfield College Flynn Union
directions: Main floor towards the back (walk on either side of the staircase and take your first turn) The all gender stalk is in between the male/female bathrooms
comment: easiest to use if you're a visitor to the campus, not super accessible if you're not, but if you walk in like you belong there (especially if you're a college age person) you should be okay

name: Slonim House Sarah Lawrence College
directions: first floor, just to the right of main entrance

name: Eastern Oregon University
directions: Badgley Hall, if you're exiting Huber auditorium (room 102) it's in the little connector hallway to your right

name: Target
directions: There are two single, gender neutral stalls located in the back of the store by the cereal and snack aisles near the food section
comment: I'm sure you could just head to bathrooms without having to buy anything

name: Lucky Platter
directions: In the back, towards the kitchen
comment: Both the "mens" and "womens" rooms are single stall and it is common practice for people of either gender to use either restroom.

name: La Principal
directions: in the back of the restraurant
comment: Just let the bartender or host know you need to use the restroom and they'll let you right on through.

name: Newport Public Library
directions: Main floor, just near the main entrance.

name: New Birds Hair Salon
street: Borchard Shopping Center, 313 Borchard Dr, Ventura, CA 93003

name: Henrietta Hudson
directions: Right on the other side of the room when you walk in through the door
comment: They are very nice and accepting of gender identities there, so you can tell them as much or as little as you want about why you're there

name: Florida Gulf Coast University Library
directions: Near the Starbucks in the library

name: Starbucks
comment: Need a bathroom code-1201

name: One Eye Jacques
directions: In the back of the shop. Not marked by any kind of gendered sign.
comment: It's very narrow and they have tables in the back, if many people are seated at the tables it won't be wheel chair accessible.

name: Drew University
directions: Single stall accessible bathroom In the Ehinger Center
comment: Open to all.

name: Starbucks
comment: Need a bathroom code, which is 1201

name: Sneaky Beans
comment: Two bathrooms, neither in view of order counter so if you prefer you can just walk past as if you're looking for someone you're meeting.

name: Geological Survey
directions: Near the door in the southeast corner of the building, from the door off of 10th street. Walk in and up the 1/2 flight of stairs. It's on the first floor, turn left, and it should be one of the first few doors on the left.

name: Uris Hall, Cornell University
directions: On the ground floor "G" in the same hallway as the women's restroom. If you're coming down the stairs from the 1st floor, go left then left again. If you're coming in on the ground floor go left and then right.
comment: Usually the building is open, and there aren't too many people inside except around class times.

name: Deep South Pops
comment: If you enter from behind (door by the picnic tables) you can access the restroom just to the left and down the hall without being in view of the ordering area.
